Whereas following the ceremony, President Ford goes immediately to work meeting with Congressional
			 leaders, senior White House staff, senior economic advisors, and foreign
			 emissaries;

Whereas on August 19, 1974, on his first Presidential trip outside of Washington, DC, President
			 Gerald R. Ford delivers an impassioned speech to the Veterans of Foreign
			 Wars Convention in Chicago;

Whereas on September 26, 1974, through September 28, 1974, President Gerald R. Ford stands strong
			 by his beloved wife First Lady Betty Ford as she courageously and openly
			 battles Breast Cancer;

